[4] Cholera - Nigeria (Borno State)
Date: Sun 2 Dec 2018
Source: Government of Nigeria [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/situation-report-cholera-outbreak-borno-state-no81-wk-48-26th-november-2nd-december


Epidemiological summary
-------------------------
The total number of suspected cholera cases reported between 26 Nov and 2 Dec 2018 stands at 6307 with 73 associated deaths (case fatality rate, 1.15%): 2442 in Jere, 1536 in MMC, 340 in Magumeri, 34 in Kaga, 166 in Konduga, 136 in Chibok, 11 in Shani, 42 in Damboa, 1052 in Ngala, 91 in Askira-Uba, 161 in Kwaya-Kusar, 56 in Bama, 57 in Dikwa, 70 in Guzamala and 121 in KalaBalge LGAs [local government areas]. No additional cases were reported from Magumeri, Ngala, Askira/Uba, Kaga, Chibok, Dikwa, Shani, Damboa, KwayaKusar, Guzamala, Konduga and Bama LGAs.

Of the 196 samples collected and tested in the state using rapid diagnostic tests, 161 (82%) were positive, and 40 (44%) of 91 samples were culture positive.

