[5] Cholera - Nigeria (Adamawa State)
Date: Tue 4 Dec 2018
Source: Government of Nigeria [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/situation-report-cholera-outbreak-adamawa-state-week-48-reported-4th-december-2018


The total number of cases reported as of 2 Dec 2018 stands at 2755 cases with 41 deaths (case fatality rate [CFR], 1.5%). Yola North has 264 cases with 6 deaths (CFR, 2.3%); Fufore has 687 cases with 7 deaths (CFR, 1.0%); Girei has 17 cases with no deaths (CFR, 0%); Yola South has 51 cases with 1 death (CFR, 2.0%); Hong has 9 cases with no deaths (CFR, 0%); Maiha has 170 cases with 1 death (CFR, 0.6%); Mubi North has 639 cases and 14 deaths (CFR, 2.2%); and Mubi South has 918 cases with 12 deaths (CFR, 1.3%). Of 73 culture samples taken, 42 yielded positive growth.

